pr_body:
The long URLs was overflowing in the info popup and causing difficulties to read the actual contents. Additionally, I aligned the content info to the right to make it look tidier.

Before;
![screen shot 2017-02-15 at 23 31 54](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/6985467/22998469/334cb4a4-f3d7-11e6-9a0f-b279f91c3035.png)

After;
![screen shot 2017-02-15 at 23 19 22](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/6985467/22998477/387076b4-f3d7-11e6-81c1-cf118af4346f.png)

- [x] closes #87
- [x] tests added / passed

@mcaceresb it could probably be improved by adding `varlist`, and maybe `if`. I figure it would take you only a couple minutes to figure out the right `argparse` line? The problem with `if` is that I don't want to export the dataset, and I'm not sure if there's a way to _first_ apply the `if` and _then_ apply the `in`. Because using both of them returns nothing if there are no observations within `in` that also meet `if`.

due to client bug when there was default value set for a field
it ended up saving something like this:

```
{
    "schema": {
        "genre": {
            "genre": {"name": "sports"},
            "default": {"name": "sports"},
            "type": "list"
        }
    }
}
```

which raises an error on publish about missing rule for `genre`.
This will make it ignore all such fields in schema.

SDESK-579
